v2.0.9: gym hours with shifts, remove subcategories, profile multi-gym

Major UX improvements + simplification:

Gym hours configuration:
- New "Configurar Horario del Gimnasio" modal with shift-based scheduling
- Each shift = (days + start + end + trainers) — single source of truth
  for both opening hours AND trainer assignments
- Slot duration selector (30 min / 1 h / 1h 30 / 2 h)
- Multiple trainers per shift (morning team / afternoon team etc.)
- Auto-deduplicates overlapping shifts so slots never double up
- Backend: class.service.setGymHours() creates/updates the special
  "Gimnasio" class transparently — owner doesn't have to know the
  internal name convention

Subcategories removed from UX:
- Exercises now live directly under a CATEGORY (no more 2-level hierarchy)
- Migration: adds exercises.category_id, backfills from existing
  subcategory chain at first launch
- ExerciseModal: single "Categoría *" required dropdown — no more
  confusing "Subcategoría (Opcional)" that was actually required
- CategorySidebar: subcategory section removed, "+ Subcategoría" button
  removed
- RoutineBuilder: subcategory filter pills removed
- Back-compat: getExercises COALESCEs the new category_id with the
  derived chain, so legacy exercises that only had subcategory_id
  still appear correctly under their category

Plus stability fixes already in code:
- License switch confirmation dialog + dbManager.wipeAllData() helper
- Zoom shortcuts hardened (Ctrl+0 / Ctrl++ / Ctrl+-)
- Multi-gym invite (no more "ya tiene cuenta" dead-end)
- Exercise validation no longer requires subcategoryId

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
